        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 12:24PM CDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 1223 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elba. The strong thunderstorm is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Level, Wise Mill, New Haven, Curtis, Carl Folsom A/p, Elba,
Danleys Crossroads, Zoar, Lee, and Newby.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
